{"id": 231305864, "title": "Glasgow cyclist 'breezed' through red light and pedestrian crossing while on phone", "text": "A Glasgow cyclist was caught running a red light and pedestrian crossing while on their phone. The rider went through the pedestrian crossing in the city centre just as people were beginning to cross the road. They were stopped by officers from Police Scotland after the incident. Road Policing Scotland shared the incident online and confirmed the cyclist was handed a fixed penalty notice by officers. READ MORE: Man found injured on Johnstone street rushed to hospital by ambulance READ MORE: Man dies on Glasgow west end street as forensic teams scour scene following 'unexplained' incident Posting on X, the force said: \"The rider of this cycle didn't care to stop for the red light as they breezed through while using their phone - and right over the pedestrian crossing where people had started to cross. \"Rider stopped and issued with a #COFPN by #GlasgowRP in #Glasgow #CityCentre.\" Join Glasgow Live's WhatsApp community here and get the latest news sent straight to your messages. Sign up to our daily Glasgow Live newsletter here to receive news and features direct to your inbox", "summary": "The rider narrowly avoided hitting anyone as he went through a pedestrian crossing in the city centre just as people were beginning to cross the road. He has now been handed a fixed penalty notice.", "url": "https://www.glasgowlive.co.uk/news/glasgow-news/glasgow-cyclist-breezed-through-red-29318629", "image": "https://i2-prod.glasgowlive.co.uk/incoming/article29318637.ece/ALTERNATES/s1200/0_GPgS0EwW4AAhNZ0jpeg.jpg", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-06-08 15:10:29", "author": "Laura Ferguson", "authors": ["Laura Ferguson"], "language": "en", "source_country": "gb", "sentiment": -0.421}